This paper deals with knowledge graph reasoning and information extraction, which are topics related to natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible sub-category as well.
